cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with automatic recognition of American Sign Language fingerspelling from video, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses neural networks and attention mechanisms, which are common in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research, so cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under the category of multimedia (MM), so cs.MM is also a possible category.
